                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12653499" author="bryanduxbury" created="Thu, 4 Dec 2008 21:41:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Turns out that there are more problems:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;i16 is affected by the same issue as byte - need a (short) cast&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;byte, i16, and i64 list types need casts when there are default values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12653512" author="bryanduxbury" created="Thu, 4 Dec 2008 22:11:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch seems to fix the problem pretty nicely. Review, please?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12657152" author="dreiss" created="Tue, 16 Dec 2008 20:29:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I had to fix it for C++ too because the test case was failing to compile.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
